\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s7\cf2\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb280\sa280\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ab\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f5\fs24\lang1033\b\loch\f5\fs24\lang1033\b {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f5\fs24\lang1033\i0\b The Merger transaction}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s7\cf2\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb280\sa280\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f5\fs24\lang1033\loch\f5\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f5\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 The Merger entails Engen acquiring 49% of the shares in the share capital of Zenex , as well as the claims on loan account  presently held by SCMB, 51% of the shares in the share capital of Wimmeria Investments, presently held by Worldwide, as well as the 
claims on loan account presently held by Worldwide, and all the shares in Waldeck Investments presently held by management.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s7\cf2\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb280\sa280\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ab\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f5\fs24\lang1033\b\loch\f5\fs24\lang1033\b {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f5\fs24\lang1033\i0\b Evaluating the merger}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s7\cf2\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb280\sa280\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f5\fs24\lang1033\loch\f5\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f5\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 In assessing a merger in terms of section 16 of the Competition Act, the Tribunal must consider\'96}
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\sb280\sa225\cf1\f4\lang1033\f4\fs24\f4\lang1025\qj a.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s7\cf1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls0\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\sb280\sa225\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0{\cf2\ltrch\hich\f5\loch\f5 whether or not the merger is likely to substantially prevent or lessen competition; and}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0{\ltrch\hich\f5\loch\f5  }}
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\sa280\cf1\f4\lang1033\f4\fs24\f4\lang1025\qj b.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s7\cf1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls0\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-360\sa280\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033{\cf2\ltrch\hich\loch{\rtlch \ltrch\loch \~}}{\cf2{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 whether the merger can or cannot be justified on substantial public interest grounds by considering the effect of the merger on each of the following: a particular industrial sector or region; employment; the ability of small businesses or firms controlle
d by historically disadvantaged persons, to become competitive; and the ability of national industries to compete in international markets.}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0{\ltrch\hich\f5\loch\f5  }}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s7\cf1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb280\sa280\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0{\cf2\ltrch\hich\f5\loch\f5 To answer the question whether the merger is likely to substantially prevent or lessen competition, the Tribunal must, in terms of Section 16(2), assess the strength of competition in the }}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0{\cf2\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f5\b\loch\f5\b relevant market}{\cf2\ltrch\hich\f5\loch\f5  and the probability that the firms in the market aft
er the merger will behave competitively or co-operatively.}}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s7\cf1{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb280\sa280\ql\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0{\cf2\ul\ulc0\ltrch\hich\f5\loch\f5 The Relevant Market}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0{\cf2\ltrch\hich\f5\loch\f5  }}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s7\cf2\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb280\sa280\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f5\fs24\lang1033\loch\f5\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f5\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 The principal business activities of Engen revolve around the refining and marketing of petroleum products. }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s7\cf1{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb280\sa280\ql\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f5\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 Zenex is a regional oil company that does not have its own refining facilities. Zenex finds itself in the vulnerable situation where it is totally dependant on its competitors for the supply of petrol and diesel and other petroleum products. In a deregulat
ed market Zenex will be unable to subsidize discounts given by its dealers, as it does not possess the upstream profit resources that rival refining companies have. This will cause Zenex\'92s service stations to become uncompetitive.    }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s7\cf1{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb280\sa280\ql\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f5\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 There are three main areas in which both Zenex and Engen are active i.e. 1) the marketing of petroleum products through retail service stations, appointed agents depots or directly to the consumer, 2) the blending and packaging of lubricants for other mark
eters of lubricants as well as for itself, 3) the storing of petroleum products for and on behalf of marketers of petroleum products.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s7\cf1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi0\sb280\sa280\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0{\cf2\ltrch\hich\f5\loch\f5 1) }}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0{\cf2\ul\ulc0\ltrch\hich\f5\loch\f5 The marketing of petroleum products}}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s7\cf2\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi0\sb280\sa280\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f5\fs24\lang1033\loch\f5\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f5\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 Seven individual product markets can be identified in the marketing of petroleum products, namely petrol/gasoline, diesel, illuminating kerosene, heavy furnace oil, bitumen, liquid petroleum gas and lubricants. Diesel can further be subdivided into 1) sale
s through retail service stations and 2) sales through short to medium term contracts to government, agriculture and the industrial sector. }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s7\cf1{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb280\sa280\ql\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f5\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 Zenex sells petrol in six provinces excluding the Northern Cape Province, the Eastern Cape Province and the Northern Province. Due to the unavailability of other market figures, the magisterial districts in the Republic will be regarded as the relevant geo
graphical markets for the sale of petrol/gasoline and diesel sold through retail service stations. }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s7\cf1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi0\sb280\sa280\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0{\cf2\ltrch\hich\f5\loch\f5 In the Tribunal\'92s opinion the merger does not pose competitive concerns in respect of diesel sold through retail service stations or for diesel sold through contracts. The price of diesel sold through retail service stations is fixed by Government regulati
on and only 0,5% of the national market share is sold through this channel. The market for diesel sold through contracts is, }}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0{\cf2\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f5\i\loch\f5\i inter alia}{\cf2\ltrch\hich\f5\loch\f5 , a deregulated market with vast countervailing purchasing power in which Engen is not a dominant player. }}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s7\cf2\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi0\sb280\sa280\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f5\fs24\lang1033\loch\f5\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f5\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 Neither is competition affected in the markets for illuminating kerosene, heavy furnace oil, bitumen and lubricants.  Zenex have small market shares in these highly competitive markets. }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s7\cf1{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\sb280\sa280\ql\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f5\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 The Tribunal will, therefore, for purposes of this decision only consider the competitive effects of the merger on the petrol/gasoline product market.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s7\cf1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi0\sb280\sa280\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f4\fs24\lang1033\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0{\cf2\ltrch\hich\f5\loch\f5 2) }}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0{\cf2\ul\ulc0\ltrch\hich\f5\loch\f5 Blending and packaging of lubricants}}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s7\cf2\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi0\sb280\sa280\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f5\fs24\lang1033\loch\f5\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f5\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 Zenex, Sasol and Agrip manage a joint venture to blend and package lubricants for Zenex itself and other marketers of lubricants. The shareholders agreement is unaffected by the merger. The Tribunal is satisfied that the merger will not have any competitiv
